Trains Around the World
Octopus Books | 1972 | ISBN 070640078X | English | 152 pages | PDF | 55.3 MB

A beautifully illustrated history of trains around the world from Stephenson's Rocket to today's examples of technical excellence, streamlining, power and speed. The book has been compiled by authors who are well-known throughout the world as authorities and enthusiasts of this colorful and fascinating subject. Electric trains, diesel trains, freight trains, passenger trains, robber barons, railway pioneers-the whole exciting story is unfolded in vivid text and pictures
